          grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
          gap: 32px !important;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </section>

  <!-- BOND AMOUNTS -->
  <section style="padding: 48px 1.5rem; background: var(--slate-50);">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px;">How Much Does a Garfield County Bail Bond Cost?</h2>

      <p style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 18px; padding: 16px; background: #f0f7ff; border-left: 3px solid var(--blue); border-radius: 4px;"><strong>Garfield County bail bond costs depend on the charge and the bail amount set by the judge or the preset bond schedule. In Oklahoma, the bail bond premium is a percentage of the total bail amount. Common bail amounts in Garfield County include approximately $1,000 for a misdemeanor DUI, $500-$5,000 for most misdemeanors, and $5,000-$50,000 or more for felony charges. Angel Bail Bonds offers competitive rates and flexible payment plans for qualifying clients.</strong></p>

      <div style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7;">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Garfield County, like all Oklahoma counties, uses a bail schedule for common offenses. This allows many misdemeanor defendants to post bond immediately after booking without waiting for a judge. For felony charges, a bond hearing before a Garfield County District Court judge is required. Bail amounts for felony cases depend on the severity of the charge, the defendant's criminal history, flight risk, and community ties.</p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">If the defendant does not post bail within the first 24 hours, they must appear before a judge who will formally set the bond amount. Garfield County processes approximately 880 bookings per year — an average of about 4 per day — making it one of the busier facilities in northwest Oklahoma. The 204-bed detention center is among the largest in the region, and its staffing of 99 officers helps ensure processing moves at a steady pace.</p>

        <h3 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px;">What Payment Methods Does Angel Bail Bonds Accept for Garfield County Bonds?</h3>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px; padding: 12px 16px; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100); border-radius: 6px;"><strong>Angel Bail Bonds accepts cash, Visa, Mastercard, Zelle, and Venmo for Garfield County bail bonds. Financing is available for qualifying clients. We can process payments over the phone, making it possible to start the release process from anywhere without driving to Enid. There are no hidden fees.</strong></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ABOUT GARFIELD COUNTY — unique local content -->
  <section style="padding: 48px 1.5rem; background: white;">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px;">Where Is the Garfield County Detention Center and How Do I Get There?</h2>
      <div style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7;">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px; padding: 12px 16px; background: #f0f7ff; border-left: 3px solid var(--blue); border-radius: 4px;"><strong>The Garfield County Detention Center is located at 1020 South 10th Street, Enid, OK 73701. The facility is operated by the Garfield County Criminal Trust Authority and has been in service since 1931. Enid is approximately 65 miles from Stillwater — about 1 hour and 8 minutes by car. The Garfield County Sheriff's Office is headquartered at 216 W. Oxford Ave, Enid, OK 73701, and can be reached at (580) 237-0244. The detention center phone is (580) 548-2429.</strong></p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Garfield County is located in north-central Oklahoma with a 2020 Census population of 62,846. Enid, the county seat, is the largest city in northwest Oklahoma with a population exceeding 51,000. Named after President James A. Garfield, the county covers a large area of farmland, oil fields, and communities established during the 1893 Cherokee Outlet land opening. Enid serves as the commercial hub of northwest Oklahoma and is home to Vance Air Force Base, a major USAF pilot training installation.</p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">In addition to Enid, Garfield County includes the communities of North Enid, Covington, Drummond, Lahoma, Waukomis, Hunter, Garber, Kremlin, Carrier, Hillsdale, Fairmont, Douglas, and Breckinridge. Whether an arrest occurs during a traffic stop on US-81, at a business in Enid, near Vance AFB, or anywhere within the Garfield County Sheriff's jurisdiction, all bookings go through the Garfield County Detention Center. Angel Bail Bonds can post bond and secure a fast release regardless of the circumstances.</p>

        <h3 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px;">How Far Is Garfield County from Stillwater?</h3>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px; padding: 12px 16px; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100); border-radius: 6px;"><strong>The Garfield County Detention Center in Enid is approximately 65 miles from Stillwater, a drive of about 1 hour and 8 minutes. Angel Bail Bonds handles Garfield County bonds regularly and can coordinate posting remotely by phone, so you may not need to drive to Enid at all. We accept payment by phone via Visa, Mastercard, Zelle, or Venmo. Se habla español.</strong></p>
      </div>

      <h3 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px;">Garfield County Communities We Serve</h3>
      <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 14px;">
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Enid</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">North Enid</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Covington</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Drummond</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Lahoma</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Waukomis</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Hunter</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Garber</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Kremlin</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Carrier</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Hillsdale</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Fairmont</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Douglas</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Breckinridge</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- COURTHOUSE + COURT INFO -->
  <section style="padding: 48px 1.5rem; background: var(--slate-50);">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px;">Garfield County Courthouse and Court Appearance Information</h2>

      <p style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 18px; padding: 16px; background: #f0f7ff; border-left: 3px solid var(--blue); border-radius: 4px;"><strong>The Garfield County Courthouse is located at 114 West Broadway Avenue, Enid, OK 73701. The Court Clerk is Janelle M. Sharp, reachable at (580) 237-0232. Office hours are Monday through Friday, 8:00 AM to 4:30 PM. Garfield County is part of Oklahoma District 4. All criminal cases are heard in the Garfield County District Court. Arraignments typically occur within 24 hours of arrest. Court dockets are available at oscn.net.</strong></p>

      <div style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7;">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">After posting bail and being released from the Garfield County Detention Center, the defendant must appear at all scheduled court hearings at the Garfield County Courthouse. Failure to appear will result in forfeiture of the bond, a bench warrant, and additional criminal charges. Angel Bail Bonds will remind you of upcoming court dates and help ensure you understand your obligations after release.</p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">For misdemeanor cases, bail is often available through a preset bond schedule, meaning the defendant can bond out immediately after booking without a judicial hearing. Felony cases require a separate bond hearing before a Garfield County District Court judge. Because Garfield County is a larger county with a high volume of cases, the courthouse maintains a regular docket schedule. Angel Bail Bonds monitors Garfield County dockets and can advise you on the expected timeline for your case.</p>
